How To Remastering Ubuntu/Linux Mint And Other Ubuntu Based

You need:
1.UCK
  $sudo apt install uck
2.Activate Modprobe squashfs
  $sudo modprobe squashfs
3.Internet Connection  For Adding Application Package Into Your New Distro
4.Base Linux Mint/Ubuntu,etc(Only Ubuntu Based)
Let's Rock Now!

1.Open Terminal and type
 $sudo uck-remaster-clean
 $cd /your-distro-base-directory
 $sudo uck-remaster-unpack-iso your_iso_base_name.iso /Your Unpacked ISO Directory Prefered
 $sudo uck-remaster-unpack-rootfs /Your Unpacked rootfs Directory Prefered
 $sudo uck-remaster-unpack-initrd /Your Unpacked initrd Directory Prefered
 $sudo uck-remaster-chroot-rootfs /Your Unpacked root user file Directory Prefered
 
